{"questionId":"9c629a63-5faf-46a6-929d-d4196f7c3150_4","correctAnswer":"21","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Apply the factoring from the given condition","content":"Note $42+7x = 7(6+x)$, and $6+x=3$."},{"title":"Compute the target value","content":"So $42+7x = 7 \\cdot 3 = 21$. The answer is <strong>21</strong>."}]}